The paper focuses on Visual Question Answering (VQA), which involves both computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel approach that involves learning to reason by routing between modules, which falls under the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG, cs.NE) sub-categories.
